'''Editorial independence''' is the [[Free will|freedom]] of [[Copy editing|editors]] to make decisions without interference from the [[owners]] of a [[publication]]. Editorial independence is tested, for instance, if a newspaper runs [[Article (publishing)|articles]] that may be unpopular with its [[advertising]] [[clientele]] or critical of its ownership.
