'''''Türk Edebiyatı''''' (translated ''Turkish Literature'') is a [[Turkish language|Turkish]] [[literary magazine]] based in [[Turkey]]. The magazine was first published on 15 January 1972.<ref name=vah/> The founder was Ahmet Kabaklı.<ref name=vah/><ref>{{cite news|title=Besir Ayvazoglu Turk Edebiyatini anlatacak|url=http://kulturgundemi.com/edebiyat/besir-ayvazoglu-turk-edebiyatini-anlatacak-haber-15648|accessdate=13 August 2015|work=Kultur Gundemi|date=3 June 2015|language=Turkish}}</ref> [[Beşir Ayvazoğlu]] served as the [[editor-in-chief]] of the magazine between 2005 and 2015.<ref name=vah>{{cite web|title=Turk Edebiyatı’na 500. sayıda nazar degdi|url=http://www.gazetevahdet.com/turk-edebiyatina-500-sayida-nazar-degdi-23644h.htm|work=Vahdet|accessdate=13 August 2015|language=Turkish|date=10 June 2015}}</ref> He was succeeded by Bahtiyar Aslan in the aforementioned post in June 2015.<ref>{{cite news|author=Kaan Burak Şen|title=Türk Edebiyatı Dergisi'nde nöbet değişimi İstanbul|url=http://www.diyadinnet.com/HABER-178723-t%C3%BCrk-edebiyat%C4%B1-dergisinde-n%C3%B6bet-de%C4%9Fi%C5%9Fimi-istanbul|accessdate=13 August 2015|work=Diyadin Net|date=26 June 2015|location=İstanbul|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150923215320/http://www.diyadinnet.com/HABER-178723-t%C3%BCrk-edebiyat%C4%B1-dergisinde-n%C3%B6bet-de%C4%9Fi%C5%9Fimi-istanbul|archivedate=23 September 2015|df=dmy-all}}</ref>

